Bonus Exalted Feats		KEY:Vow of Poverty ~ Bonus Exalted Feats					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality																DESC:At 1st level, an ascetic gets a bonus exalted feat, and another bonus feat at 2nd level and every 2 levels thereafter. Unlike the other benefits of a vow of poverty, a character does not gain these bonus feats retroactively when he takes the Vow of Poverty feat; he only gains those bonus feats that apply for the levels he gains after swearing his vow. Thus, the bonus feat gained at 1st level is available only to humans who take both Sacred Vow and Vow of Poverty at 1st level.																																																																																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.30
Endure Elements			KEY:Vow of Poverty ~ Endure Elements					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary														DESC:A 3rd-level ascetic is immune to the effects of being in a hot or cold environment. He can exist comfortably in conditions between -50 and 140 degrees Fahrenheit without having to make Fortitude saves (as described in the Dungeon Master's Guide).																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.30
Exalted Strike			KEY:Vow of Poverty ~ Exalted Strike						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural						DEFINE:VowOfPovertyExaltedStrikeBonus|0		DESC:At 4th level, an ascetic gains a +1 enhancement bonus on all his attack and damage rolls. In effect, any weapon the character wields becomes a +1 magic weapon, and can overcome the damage reduction of a creature as though it were a magic weapon. This enhancement bonus rises to +2 at 10th level, to +3 at 14th level, to +4 at 17th level, and to +5 at 20th level. At 10th level, any weapon damage the character deals is also considered to be good-aligned, so that it can bypass the damage reduction of some evil outsiders.	DESC:+%1 (magic)|VowOfPovertyExaltedStrikeBonus|PREVAREQ:VowOfPovertyExaltedStrikeBonus,1	DESC:+%1 (Magic &amp; Good)|VowOfPovertyExaltedStrikeBonus|PREVARGTEQ:VowOfPovertyExaltedStrikeBonus,2																											BONUS:VAR|VowOfPovertyExaltedStrikeBonus|1|PREPCLEVEL:MIN=4	BONUS:VAR|VowOfPovertyExaltedStrikeBonus|1|PREPCLEVEL:MIN=10	BONUS:VAR|VowOfPovertyExaltedStrikeBonus|1|PREPCLEVEL:MIN=14	BONUS:VAR|VowOfPovertyExaltedStrikeBonus|1|PREPCLEVEL:MIN=17	BONUS:VAR|VowOfPovertyExaltedStrikeBonus|1|PREPCLEVEL:MIN=20							BONUS:WEAPONPROF=TYPE.Simple|TOHIT,DAMAGE|VowOfPovertyExaltedStrikeBonus|TYPE=Enhancement	BONUS:WEAPONPROF=TYPE.Martial|TOHIT,DAMAGE|VowOfPovertyExaltedStrikeBonus|TYPE=Enhancement	BONUS:WEAPONPROF=TYPE.Exotic|TOHIT,DAMAGE|VowOfPovertyExaltedStrikeBonus|TYPE=Enhancement	BONUS:WEAPONPROF=TYPE.Natural|TOHIT,DAMAGE|VowOfPovertyExaltedStrikeBonus|TYPE=Enhancement																		SOURCEPAGE:p.30
